---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { SITE } from "../../config/site";

const title = "Biweekly Payments vs Extra Principal (which saves more?)";
const description =
  "Biweekly mortgage payments can act like an extra payment per year, but results depend on how your lender applies them. Educational use only.";
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} canonicalPath="/guides/biweekly-vs-extra-principal">
  <section class="card hero">
    <span class="pill">Guide</span>
    <nav class="breadcrumbs" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <a href="/">Home</a>
      <span aria-hidden="true">/</span>
      <a href="/guides">Guides</a>
      <span aria-hidden="true">/</span>
      <span aria-current="page">Biweekly vs extra principal</span>
    </nav>
    <h1>Biweekly vs extra principal</h1>
    <p>
      True biweekly payments (every two weeks) create 26 half-payments per year, which equals 13 full payments. That can
      reduce interest and shorten payoff time. But some lender “biweekly programs” just hold funds and pay monthly, which
      can reduce the benefit.
    </p>
    <div class="btn-row">
      <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/calculators/extra-payment-calculator">Compare scenarios</a>
      <a class="btn" href="/guides/one-extra-mortgage-payment-per-year">One extra payment per year</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="grid" style="margin-top:18px">
    <div class="card section prose col-6">
      <h2 style="margin-top:0">When biweekly helps</h2>
      <ul class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0; padding-left:18px">
        <li>Payments are applied as principal-and-interest every two weeks.</li>
        <li>You avoid a “fee-based” third-party program.</li>
        <li>You prefer automatic consistency over choosing a monthly extra.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="card section prose col-6">
      <h2 style="margin-top:0">When it may not</h2>
      <ul class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0; padding-left:18px">
        <li>The lender holds payments and posts them monthly (less interest savings).</li>
        <li>There are service fees that eat into savings.</li>
        <li>Your cash flow is uneven and biweekly causes overdrafts.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="card section prose" style="margin-top:18px">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">A simple comparison method</h2>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0">
      In practice, many people compare biweekly to an equivalent monthly extra. If a full payment is $P, then one extra
      payment per year is about $P/12 per month. Model that monthly extra and compare it to your baseline.
    </p>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:12px 0 0">
      Use the <a href="/calculators/extra-payment-calculator">Extra Payment Mortgage Calculator</a> to test an extra amount and
      sanity-check with the <a href="/calculators/amortization-schedule-calculator">Amortization Schedule Calculator</a>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card section prose" style="margin-top:18px">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">Biweekly vs monthly extra (quick comparison)</h2>
    <div style="overflow:auto; margin-top:12px">
      <table class="table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Option</th>
            <th>What happens</th>
            <th>Risk / gotchas</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>True biweekly</td>
            <td>13 payments per year (26 half payments), often slightly earlier principal reduction.</td>
            <td>Confirm posting cadence; avoid fee-based programs.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Monthly extra</td>
            <td>Add a fixed principal-only amount each month.</td>
            <td>Must be applied as principal-only (not “paid ahead”).</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="card section prose" style="margin-top:18px">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">What to ask your lender</h2>
    <ul class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0; padding-left:18px">
      <li>Are biweekly payments posted immediately or held and posted monthly?</li>
      <li>Is the “extra” applied as principal-only?</li>
      <li>Are there fees, and can you cancel easily?</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:12px 0 0">
      For questions, email <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}>{SITE.email}</a>.
    </p>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:12px 0 0; font-size:13px">Last updated: 2026-01-25</p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
